Nigeria Seeking 15 Trillion-Naira in Investment, ThisDay Says

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-07-12T09:04:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/nigeria-seeking-15-trillion-naira-in-investment-thisday-says.html
Nigeria hopes to attract 15 trillion
naira ($99 billion) in private investment in the next four
years,  ThisDay  cited the Investment and Trade Ministry as saying
in a statement.  The new ministry, which was formed from the Commerce and
Industry Ministry, is headed by Olusegun Aganga, former finance
minister, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 